Television actress, Motsoaledi Setumo sent a heart warming messages to her queen mother. The 28-year-old actress who currently plays the role of Mmabatho on Mzansi Magic’s telenovela The Queen shared a touching message about the tragic incident that affected her mum’s  ability to walk. The tweet read:  “With everything she’s been through look how happy my Queen looks. 20 years on this damn chair cause some drunk driver decided to skip a red traffic light.” She added that it truly takes a village to raise a child. “I’m that child! A Glenda Setumo Appreciation Tweet,” she said. The actress and radio host further mentioned that her mum amazes her from time to time.  